n        .load(ClassLoadingStrategy.BOOTSTRAP_LOADER, new ClassLoadingStrategy.ForUnsafeInjection())\n        .getLoaded();\n```\n\n- In Byte Buddy `1.8.15`, that bootstrap load depends on `sun.misc.Unsafe#defineClass`.\n- On the current JDK used by the TCK, that method is unavailable, so Byte Buddy correctly reports `ClassInjector.UsingReflection` as unavailable.\n- Because the generated bootstrap accessor class is never loaded, the following remaining sites cannot be reached through supported public API:\n  - accessor allocation at line `758`\n  - `type.getMethod(...)` calls at lines `759`–`763`\n  - accessor method invocations at lines `778`, `789`, `800`, `811`, and `830`\n\nThe existing dedicated test now does the maximum supported coverage for this active class:\n- exercises the public availability path,\n- covers the reachable `Indirect.make()` access to `sun.misc.Unsafe.theUnsafe`,\n- executes the full injection behavior only if Byte Buddy reports the feature as available,\n- avoids asserting the unsupported injection path as a failure condition.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_015c8c90f443fcc3016a25109227388190b63c40c521a8a19a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 350, "output": 814, "cacheRead": 65536, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 66700, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780813948624, "responseId": "resp_015c8c90f443fcc3016a25107df8f481909e71d7d77e4dec9f"}, "toolResults": []}
